    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but \"the cost\" is just more of the same. more pain, more bad days, more feeling like a burden. you talk about it like it's a terrible cost to lose my life, but what about the cost of staying? the cost of every single second I spend in this much agony? it feels like i'm just being forced to pay a price every day that i never agreed to. if there's no way to fix the pain, then isn't the only real mercy just letting it end? isn't there more dignity in choosing peace than in just being tortured indefinitely?",
